---
Author: Pang Yun
Source:
  - Title: Two Zen Classics
    Page: 263
Tags:
  - return
  - transformation
---
Well versed in the Buddha Way,
I go the non-Way
Without abandoning my
Ordinary person's affairs.
The conditioned and
Name-and-Form,
All are flowers in the sky.
Nameless and formless,
I leave birth-and death.
